In .NET 10, MAUI adopted **edge-to-edge** rendering on Android, and `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` (which backed `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize`) was deprecated by Android in API 30. The layout no longer automatically shrinks when the keyboard opens.

## Recommended fix for .NET 10

**Use `WindowInsets` to adjust your layout's bottom padding:**

### 1. In your Android platform code (Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs):

```csharp
using Android.Views;
using AndroidX.Core.View;
using Microsoft.Maui.Controls.Compatibility.Platform.Android;

public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity
{
    protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
    {
        base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

        // Ensure edge-to-edge insets are dispatched
        WindowCompat.SetDecorFitsSystemWindows(Window!, false);

        var rootView = Window!.DecorView.FindViewById(Android.Resource.Id.Content)!;
        ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(rootView, new KeyboardInsetsListener());
    }
}

class KeyboardInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
{
    public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(Android.Views.View v, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
    {
        var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
        var navInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.NavigationBars());

        // Use the larger of keyboard or nav bar height
        int bottomPadding = Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom, navInsets.Bottom);
        v.SetPadding(0, 0, 0, bottomPadding);

        return insets;
    }
}
```

### 2. Keep your `AndroidManifest.xml` soft input mode as `adjustResize`:

```xml
<activity
    android:windowSoftInputMode="adjustResize"
    ... />
```

### 3. Your XAML layout (simplified chat screen):

```xml
<Grid RowDefinitions="*, Auto">
    <CollectionView Grid.Row="0" ItemsSource="{Binding Messages}" ... />

    <HorizontalStackLayout Grid.Row="1" Padding="8">
        <Entry Placeholder="Type a message..." HorizontalOptions="FillAndExpand" />
        <Button Text="Send" />
    </HorizontalStackLayout>
</Grid>
```

## Alternative: MAUI's built-in scroll behavior

If your `Entry` is inside a `ScrollView`, MAUI's `KeyboardAutoManagerScroll` will scroll to keep the focused element visible. You can disable/enable it per-page:

```csharp
KeyboardAutoManagerScroll.Disconnect(); // disable
KeyboardAutoManagerScroll.Connect();    // re-enable
```

---

**TL;DR:** Replace the old resize mode with a `WindowInsets` listener that applies the IME (keyboard) bottom inset as padding on the root view. This is the Android-recommended pattern going forward.
